Odisha Panchayat Election Results 2017-Live Updates: Stakes high for BJP, Congress, BJD Odisha Panchayat Election Results 2017-Live Updates: Stakes high for BJP, Congress, BJD Bharatiya Janata Party is learnt to have won nearly 306 seats, ten times its tally in the last election. While the Congress' performance has gone down, falling from 126 to 66, the ruling BJD also saw a fall from 651 to 460 seats. By: FE Online | New Delhi | Published: February 25, 2017 11:16 AM As per reports, Bharatiya Janata Party is learnt to have won nearly 306 seats, ten times its tally in the last election. (Source: PTI) 
The Odisha state election commission will soon declare the results of the elections to the panchayats and zilla parishad seats in the state. 851 seats of Odisha had gone to polls between February 13 and 21. Many districts, including Malkangiri, Bolangir, Sambalpur, Bargarh, Deogarh and Mayurbhanj. As per reports, Bharatiya Janata Party is learnt to have won nearly 306 seats, ten times its tally in the last election. While the Congress â€™ performance has gone down, falling from 126 to 66, the ruling BJD also saw a fall from 651 to 460 seats.
